<br>
Greetings!<br>
<br>
The Ring of Mystic Souls is inviting all adventurers of season 45-52 to join our crusade against Lady Vox. We will launch the assault on January 11th, 15EST/20GMT. The forces will assemble near the main entrance to Permafrost BEFORE 15 EST. First groups will head towards the lair at 15 EST. In case we believe we lack the power to slay the dragon the raid will be cancelled.<br>
<br>
To join us you must have appropriate dragon-fighter gear ((MR and CR resistance)) and sign up below.<br>
<br>
Also, we desperately seek competent monks (below season 52) who would be so kind as to aid us with pre-clearing. Please contact Skafid or Aelros or send a message to my EZinbox. We will be more than glad to cover any reasonable fee for the services performed.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
DISCLAIMER:<br>
<br>
We cannot guarante success. Even if we do our best its possible that we will all die. In such case we will try to provide rogues for getting the bodies, coffins  (at least 15) and ressurections.<br>
<br>
<br>
LOOT POLICY:<br>
<br>
All items will be rolled on Need-before-Greed basis, meanining that all those who can and WILL use an item can roll /random 1000. Loot will be splitted after the raid in the Nexus.<br>
<br>
BASIC STRATEGY:<br>
<br>
1. All please join chat Voxraid - all chat should go there, preferably role-playing . The raid channel (/rsay) is for important messages only, if you are unsure what is important, use chat (Voxraid).<br>
<br>
2. Stick to your group. If you have questions or problems contact the groupleader. Familiarize yourself with the layout of Permafrost - we will NOT rescue those who fall in the pits till the raid is over.<br>
<br>
3. Elemental blankets, runed daggers and elemental defenders will most likely be available before the raid. If your MR is lower than 100 (unbuffed) you will spend most of the time feared. If your CR is too low you will die quickly. Consider buying holy cake and Kaladim's Constitutional - they are a great way to improve your resistances.<br>
<br>
4. Once the groups are assembled the raid will start moving towards the ice giant quarters. A separate team will slay goblins and giants to clear the path. We will not do raid-scale buffing till we reach the so-called &quot;prep room&quot;. Ask your group mates for help with buffing - toughest thing you will face on path to the &quot;prep-room&quot; will be goblins and possibly a lone evil barbarian.<br>
<br>
<br>
5. Once we reach the large corridor before the &quot;prep-room&quot; all groups will stop and the buffing group will assemble. Ask your group memebrs to cast some junk buffs on you - order of buffs is no longer important. &quot;Junk buffs&quot; include: all kinds of vision enhancement, resistances to disease, poison and fire, enduring breath and many others. Then groups will proceed one by one and receive a hp buff, haste and resist buff. Shaman's buffs are useful, we will try to provide them as well, but no guarantees here. KEI, clarity and such are not important during the dragon fight, but maigcs that increase the mana pool are useful. Buffing must be done as efficiently as possible - buffs will not be recasted! Try filling 14 buff slots before the fight, always leave the 15th free.<br>
<br>
6. Once buffed sit by the wall near your group leader. Switch run to walk, so you do not wander away far when feared. If you have resistant discipline prepare it.<br>
<br>
7. When buffing is done we will proceed to the dragon lair immediately. All groups will attack Vox. Use /disc resistant when entering the lair. (Or fearless should you prefer)<br>
<br>
8. The main assist group will head inside 3 seconds before the rest. Initial healing will likely be performed using the Lay on Hands power of paladins.<br>
<br>
9. Unless you are the MA , stay under the tail of the dragon - this way you will avoid his breath. Do not taunt! If you are a melee fighter keep hitting her like there is no tomorow right the moment you get near her.<br>
<br>
10. Vox is a healer, chanters are encouraged to drain her mana, but be very careful about not getting her attention. All magic slingers should simply start blasting when she is down to 70-60% health. You MUST be in melee range to land a spell on her! Forget about casting cold based spells, magic is often resisted but fire seems to work. Stay under her tail.<br>
<br>
11. If you are feared, wait patiently till the effect wears off and rush back into the lair - we fight till the last of us or Vox fall. If we all die we will organise coffins and go back to the entrance of Permafrost.<br>
<br>
12 If we win, the raid leader or nominated looter will take the stuff from the dragon, then porters will get us out and split takes place in the Nexus.<br>
<br>
<br>
To win we need at least 25 adventurers for the final fight, preferably 30 or more. Two clerics are a bare minimum as well as 3 bards. Without them we stand no chance. <p><img border=0 src="http://members.chello.pl/b.matejesiek/skafidsig.gif" /></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skafidfv>SkafidFV</A> at: 1/9/04 4:03 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=luinefv>Luinefv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/7/04 11:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=811.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  Lady Vox, Sunday January 11th, 15EST/20GMT/21CET OPEN</span><hr size=1> I will be present and am looking foward to this!<br>
